    "cross_module_architecture": {
      "evidence": [
        "In `goseg/system/wifi/service/c2c_service.go`, `ProcessC2CMessage` unmarshals into `structs.WsC2cPayload` and immediately dispatches by `payload.Payload.Action` without validating the message envelope contract.",
        "The same file does not verify `payload.Type` even though the wire payload type is modeled as part of the schema (`goseg/structs/WsC2cPayload` includes `Type string`), allowing transport/type mistakes to be interpreted as C2C actions.",
        "Tests in `goseg/system/wifi/service/c2c_service_test.go` cover unsupported/invalid JSON and factory errors, but do not assert that non-`c2c` envelope types are rejected before action parsing."
      ],
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "confidence": "high",
      "issues_preventing_higher_score": ""
    }
  },
  "findings": [
    {
      "dimension": "cross_module_architecture",
      "identifier": "cx_arc_001",
      "summary": "C2C payload processing ignores envelope type, weakening protocol boundary enforcement between transport and action dispatch.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/system/wifi/service/c2c_service.go",
        "goseg/system/wifi/service/c2c_service_test.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`ProcessC2CMessage` unmarshals into `structs.WsC2cPayload` and dispatches on `payload.Payload.Action` only.",
        "No check exists for `payload.Type == \"c2c\"` or any namespace/type guard before calling `ParseC2CAction` and `service.Execute(...)`.",
        "Tests assert JSON/action/`nil` factory behavior but do not include an envelope-type mismatch case."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Enforce message contract at the C2C module boundary: validate `payload.Type` against the expected namespace/token before action parsing, return a typed unsupported/contract error on mismatch, and add a unit test that a non-`c2c` message is rejected deterministically.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "c2c_message_contract_boundary"
    }
  ],
